The question isn’t who is going to let us; it’s who is going to stop us.

I started out as a little girl in the stands that never knew wrestling in carver was possible. As of this weekend, I wrestled my first match in that same place. The amount of relentless work that was done to create this reality of mine is unimaginable. It’s time to empower and give girls a future to work for. For the woman that bravely blazed the trail before us, for my teammates and opponents that step on the mat with me, and for the little girls in the stands with the biggest dreams, this one is for you. This one is for her.
The gang is what I trust❤️‍🔥
